Hi @laviedefedra! You're already on your way to becoming a member, you just still need to take a few more steps ✅ 

You have already taken the first one, which is joining our spaces: like discord, twitter, or the forum. Now, you need to be onboarded. Tomorrow is the Orientation Call, if you join we will explain to you what we do in the TEC and give you all the information you need to get started. You'll have to do some self learning: like reading our Gitbook, to better understand how our community functions. At this point you'll be what we call a Newcomer. 

To become a full-fledged member you will lastly need to participate in three different layers of our community:

* Cultural layer: 
- Praise someone 

* Governance layer:
- Sign the covenant 

* Economic layer:
- Connect wallet with Praise system 
- Hold TEC tokens 

Don't worry if it seems a lot. It is actually a simple organic process that you'll understand along the way. Tomorrow at the Orientation Call we will answer all your questions and guide you 😁

Hello @sirpy! 

In the TEC, proposals like the one you are making have to go through what we call the Advice Process. 

You would need to gather information on who would your proposal affect, and how would it affect them. After that you would consult with other stakeholders and those with expertise in the area of interest to check if your proposal if feasible. If everything seems fine, then you would finally make the proposal you want to make. 

This process is to make sure that every proposal is in touch with the reality of TEC and its members. 

As I see that you are newcomer, what I recommend you do first is to join our Orientation Call, tomorrow at 7PM CET. There you will learn about our working groups and you'll find which of them is the right place for you to start. 

Hope to see you there! 😄
